lay.pl?index=E000221|publisher=Biographical Directory of the United States Congress|accessdate=24 February 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Lucy Fato]] - (1991) - Corporate attorney, [[general counsel]] of [[AIG]] (2017\u2013present)<ref name=\"Pitt Law\">{{cite web |title=McGraw Hill Financial Appoints Pitt Law Alum Lucy Fato Executive Vice President and General Counsel |url=https://www.law.pitt.edu/mcgraw-hill-financial-appoints-pitt-law-alum-lucy-fato-executive-vice-president-and-general-counsel |website=[[University of Pittsburgh School of Law]] |accessdate=October 19, 2019 |date=September 24, 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Tom Feeney]] - (1983) - [[United States House of Representatives|U.S. Representative]] (2003\u20132009)<ref>{{cite web|title=Tom Feeney|url=http://bioguide.congress.gov/scripts/biodisplay.pl?index=f000447|publisher=Biographical Directory of the United States Congress|accessdate=26 February 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Melissa Hart (politician)|Melissa Hart]] - (1987) - [[United States House of Representatives|U.S. Representative]] (2001\u20132007)<ref>{{cite web|title=Melissa Hart|url=http://www.nndb.com/people/068/000038951/|publisher=Notable Names Data Base|accessdate=26 February 2013}}</ref>\n* [[Orrin Hatch]] - (1962) - [[President pro tempore of the United States Senate|President Pro Tempore of the U.S. Senate]] and [[United States Senate|U.S. Senator]] (1976\u2013present)<ref>{{cite web|title=Orrin Hatch|url=http://bioguide.congress.gov/scripts/biodisplay.pl?index=h000338|publisher=Biographical Directory of the United States Congress|accessdate=24 February 2013}}</ref> \n*[[Mark R. Hornak]] - (1981) - Judge for the [[United States District Court for the Western District of Pennsylvania]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Mark R. Hornak|url=http://www.fjc.gov/servlet/nGetInfo?jid=3398&cid=999&ctype=na&instate=na|publisher=Federal Judicial Center|accessdate=26 February 2013}}</ref>\n*[[K. Leroy Irvis]] - (1953) - first African American to serve as a speaker of the house (Pennsylvania) in any 