ord|title=Joseph H. Thompson|date=April 1928|publisher=University of Pittsburgh|volume=2|number=3|accessdate=February 23, 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Dick Thornburgh]] - (1957) - [[Pennsylvania Governor]] (1979\u20131987), [[United States Attorney General|U.S. Attorney General]] (1988\u20131991)<ref>{{cite web|title=Dick Thornburgh|url=http://www.nndb.com/people/636/000023567/|publisher=Notable Names Data Base|accessdate=24 February 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Debra Todd]] - (1982) - Justice on the [[Pennsylvania Supreme Court]] (2007\u2013present)<ref>{{cite web|title=Debra Todd|url=http://votesmart.org/candidate/biography/77446/debra-mccloskey-todd#.US0ZDKV--BE|publisher=Project Vote Smart|accessdate=26 February 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Dennis Unkovic]] \u2014 (1973) \u2014 International business advisor, partner at Meyer, Unkovic & Scott and author of six books{{cn|date=February 2020}}\n*[[Cyril Wecht]] - (1962) - American forensic pathologist<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.pittmag.pitt.edu/?p=1821|title=Class Notes|journal=Pitt Magazine|date=Winter 2010|publisher=University of Pittsburgh|accessdate=February 23, 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Joseph F. Weis, Jr.]] - (1950) - [[U.S. Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit]]  1973-1988<ref>http://www.post-gazette.com/local/region/2014/03/19/Former-Judge-Joseph-Weis-dies-at-91/stories/201403190178</ref>\n*[[Mary Jo White (Pennsylvania politician)|Mary Jo White]] - (1967) - [[Pennsylvania State Senate|Pennsylvania State Senator]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Mary Jo White|url=http://votesmart.org/candidate/biography/9788/mary-jo-white|publisher=Project Vote Smart|accessdate=24 February 2013}}</ref>\n*[[James A. Wright]] - (1927) - [[United States House of Representatives|U.S. Representative]] (1941\u20131945)<ref>{{cite web|title=James A. Wright|url=http://bioguide.congress.gov/scripts/biodisplay.pl?index=W000762|publisher=Biographical Directory of the United States Congress|accessdate=24 February 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Joseph \"Chip\" Yablonski]] - (1965) - Attorney, [[National Football League Players Association|NFL Players Association]]; son of murdered labor leader [[Joseph Yablonski]]<ref>{{cite book|url=http://digital.library.pitt.edu/cgi-bin/t/text/pageviewer-idx?xc=1;didno=1965e49956;cc=pittcommence;idno=1965e49956;view=image;seq=0031|title=1965 University of Pittsburgh Commencement|page=31|date=June 7, 1965|publisher=University of Pittsburgh|accessdate=February 26, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website}}\n\n{{University of Pittsburgh}}\n{{Law Schools of the Mid-Atlantic States}}\n{{coord|40.441885|-79.955707|region:US-PA_type:edu|display=title}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:University Of Pittsburgh School Of Law}}\n[[Category:University of Pittsburgh|Law, School of]]\n[[Category:Law schools in Pennsylvania|Pittsburgh, University of]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1895]]\n[[Category:1895 establishments in Pennsylvania]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_Pittsburgh_School_of_Law"}
